<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="297" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1431,1855]" pageId="16" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,305,1431,1458]" pageId="16" pageNumber="297">Distribution.</emphasis>
In the northern GOM, this species occurs from southern Florida to the Texas/ 
<collectingCountry box="[1208,1293,1432,1458]" name="Mexico" pageId="16" pageNumber="297">Mexico</collectingCountry>
border. It is usually reported from waters 
<quantity box="[479,598,1468,1495]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.45" metricValueMax="10.0" metricValueMin="0.9" pageId="16" pageNumber="297" unit="m" value="54.5" valueMax="100.0" valueMin="9.0">9 to 100 m</quantity>
in depth in the northern GOM, although NMFS SEFSC trawl surveys have captured them as deep as 
<specimenCount box="[438,509,1504,1530]" pageId="16" pageNumber="297" type="generic">
<quantity box="[438,505,1504,1530]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.3" pageId="16" pageNumber="297" unit="m" value="130.0">130m</quantity>
.
</specimenCount>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1431,1855]" pageId="16" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,470,1539,1566]" pageId="16" pageNumber="297">First Record in GOM.</emphasis>
The first recorded capture of this species in the northern GOM was by 
<bibRefCitation author="Springer, S. &amp; Bullis, Jr., H. R." pageId="16" pageNumber="297" pagination="134" refId="ref20290" refString="Springer, S. &amp; Bullis, Jr., H. R. (1956) Collections by the Oregon in the Gulf of Mexico. United States Fish and Wildlife Service Special Scientific Report: Fisheries, 196, 134." type="journal article" year="1956">Springer and Bullis (1956)</bibRefCitation>
. Individuals were captured aboard the RV 
<collectingRegion box="[775,859,1576,1602]" country="United States of America" name="Oregon" pageId="16" pageNumber="297">Oregon</collectingRegion>
on either side of the mouth of the 
<collectingRegion box="[1240,1368,1576,1602]" country="United States of America" name="Mississippi" pageId="16" pageNumber="297">Mississippi</collectingRegion>
River in approximately 
<quantity box="[349,399,1611,1638]" metricMagnitude="1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" pageId="16" pageNumber="297" unit="m" value="55.0">55m</quantity>
of water.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="297" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1431,1855]" pageId="16" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1648,1674]" pageId="16" pageNumber="297">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Whitley, 1933" authorityName="Whitley" authorityYear="1933" box="[443,741,1648,1674]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Bathytoshia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="297" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[443,577,1648,1674]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="297">Bathytoshia</emphasis>
Whitley, 1933
</taxonomicName>
was formerly considered a junior synonym of 
<taxonomicName authority="Rafinesque, 1810" authorityName="Rafinesque" authorityYear="1810" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Dasyatis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="297" phylum="Chordata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1260,1358,1649,1674]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="297">Dasyatis</emphasis>
Rafinesque, 1810
</taxonomicName>
until resurrected by 
<bibRefCitation author="Last, P. &amp; White, W. T. &amp; de Carvalho, M. R. &amp; Seret, B. &amp; Stehmann, M. F. W. &amp; Naylor, G. J. P." box="[512,702,1684,1711]" pageId="16" pageNumber="297" refId="ref18676" refString="Last, P., White, W. T., de Carvalho, M. R., Seret, B., Stehmann, M. F. W. &amp; Naylor, G. J. P. (Eds.), (2016) Rays of the World. CSIRO publishing. Melbourne, 790 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.1071 / 9780643109148" type="book" year="2016">
Last 
<emphasis box="[566,621,1684,1710]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="297">et al.</emphasis>
(2016)
</bibRefCitation>
based on morphological and molecular evidence. Eastern Atlantic specimens formerly attributed to this species are now considered a separate species, 
<taxonomicName authority="(Garman, 1880)" baseAuthorityName="Garman" baseAuthorityYear="1880" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Bathytoshia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="297" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lata">
<emphasis box="[1132,1320,1720,1746]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="297">Bathytoshia lata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Garman, S." pageId="16" pageNumber="297" pagination="167 - 172" refId="ref17218" refString="Garman, S. (1880) New species of selachians in the museum collection. Bulletin of the Museum of Comparative Zoology at Harvard College, 6 (11), 167 - 172." type="journal article" year="1880">Garman, 1880</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Mitchill" baseAuthorityYear="1815" box="[287,537,1756,1782]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Bathytoshia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="297" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="centroura">
<emphasis box="[287,537,1756,1782]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="297">Bathytoshia centroura</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
being restricted to the western Atlantic.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1437,1431,1855]" pageId="16" pageNumber="297">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,450,1791,1818]" pageId="16" pageNumber="297">Conservation Status.</emphasis>
Least Concern (when assessed together with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Garman" baseAuthorityYear="1880" box="[976,1162,1792,1818]" class="Chondrichthyes" family="Dasyatidae" genus="Bathytoshia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Myliobatiformes" pageId="16" pageNumber="297" phylum="Chordata" rank="species" species="lata">
<emphasis box="[976,1162,1792,1818]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="297">Bathytoshia lata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the eastern Atlantic).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
